race.description: The Victoria Hotel Port Fairy Hcp (Bm62)
race.comment: Tough race. BUBION (10) was a dominant maiden winner at Mt Gambier two back, not bad in what looks a stronger race at Mornington last time behind the talented Street Artist, only beaten 1.6 lengths there. Back to 1000m should suit and she'll take catching. EXUMA (2) resumes. His form tapered off at the end of last campaign but there are bits and pieces there to say he's capable on his day and both of his wins have come first up. NIGHTIME STAR (12) is going the right way and back in trip could prove beneficial for the sharp filly from an ideal draw. SELF SERVE (8) was sound fresh at Mornington and should be fitter. Stays at 1000m but has claims.
